          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 9 in. by 6, consisting of 149 leaves, the first of which is
                        much torn. The quires, 15 in number, are signed with letters from <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܘ</foreign> to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܠ</foreign>;
                        so that half the volume is missing. A single leaf is wanting after fol. 141.
                        There are from 26 to 32 lines in each page. This manuscript is dated <origDate datingMethod="Seleucid" when-custom="1177">A. Gr. 1177</origDate>, <origDate calendar="Gregorian" when="0866">A.D. 866</origDate>; but fol. <locus from="1">1</locus> is a
                        somewhat later addition.</p>
